# 6. `cache/` — Caching Layer

## Purpose

Stores frequently used data temporarily.

---

## Why Caching?

Improves performance by reducing repeated operations.

---

## Responsibilities

✅ Faster responses
✅ Reduced database load
✅ Temporary storage

---

## Example File

```plaintext id="7qydsk"
src/cache/cache_manager.py
```

---

## Example Code

```python id="d0dj0y"
cache = {}

def set_cache(key, value):

    cache[key] = value

def get_cache(key):

    return cache.get(key)
```

